        .

I will end with a quotation, which will be familiar to my compatriot Mr Almunia: 'Publish not many edicts; 
          when
         you do enact pragmatics and decrees, see that they be good ones and, above all, that they are well observed', so said Don Quixote to his friend Sancho.

